The lower boundary, Γ1, of the brain tissue in the model lies adjacent to brain tissue in neighboring regions. Therefore, boundary Γ1 has to be constrained accordingly. The applied constraint on Γ1 is obtained by tying all nodal displacements on Γ1 to a linear interpolation between the displacements of corner nodes C1 and C2. For any node on boundary Γ1, this results in11\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
