The loading conditions of the cerebral cortex model (micro-level in Fig. 4) are based on the loading conditions that have been used by Brands et al.6 for a three-dimensional numerical head model (macro-level in Fig. 4). In that model, an eccentric rotation has been applied to the skull to simulate an angular head acceleration around the neck-shoulder joint in the sagittal plane in the anterior–posterior direction. The eccentricity has been chosen to represent a typical neck length. The axis of rotation has been positioned at 155 mm below the anatomical origin, i.e., the ear hole projected to the sagittal plane. The rotation of the head model consists of two successive sine functions that describe the angular acceleration:12\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
